author: Chao Deng
title: Asian Shares Make Tepid Start
text:
Markets in Asia had a lackluster start Thursday, as investors balanced signals of a weaker U.S. recovery with chances that the Federal Reserve will delay an interest-rate increase into next year.
The Nikkei Stock Average was up 0.4%, South Korea’s Kospi gained 0.8% and Australia’s S&P ASX 200 gained 0.7%.
